---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Ivytree Essex Case Study">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[68ch] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-12 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Top Bar Navigation -->
    <div class="text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-4">
      <a href="/work" class="hover:text-[#FAFAFA] transition-colors">← Back to Work</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Header Section -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="flex gap-2 text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
        <span>Professional Work</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>2024</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-tight">
        Ivytree Essex
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] italic">
        "A high-performance educational portal built to simplify content updates and registration flows."
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Project Snapshot -->
    <section class="border-y border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] py-6 text-xs font-mono text-[#A1A1AA] flex flex-col gap-2">
      <div>Role: <span class="text-white">Full Stack Engineer</span></div>
      <div>Duration: <span class="text-white">Jan 2024 – Apr 2024</span></div>
      <div>Status: <span class="text-white">● Production</span></div>
      <div>Team: <span class="text-white">1 Engineer</span></div>
      <div>Stack: <span class="text-white">Next.js · Strapi CMS · PostgreSQL</span></div>
      <div>Repository: <span class="text-white">Private</span></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Case Study Sections -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-12 text-[#FAFAFA] text-base leading-[1.7] tracking-tight font-normal">
      
      <!-- 1. Executive Summary -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">01. Executive Summary</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          Ivytree Essex is an educational portal built to manage student course schedules, class registration details, and parent communication resources. The project focused on integrating a headless Strapi CMS to allow non-technical staff to update content securely.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 2. Goals -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">02. Goals</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          Success looked like a load time under two seconds, a robust SEO profile, and a simple dashboard for editors to manage course tables without code changes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 3. Architecture -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">03. Architecture</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          We implemented a headless Strapi CMS running alongside a PostgreSQL database, fetching content parameters during Next.js static page generation builds.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 4. Challenges -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">04. Challenges</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          The primary engineering hurdle was managing large file assets and image uploads without bloating the static build compilation times or degrading CDN delivery.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 5. Outcome -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">05. Outcome</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          The portal successfully processed enrollment signups and provided parents with fast access to schedules.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 6. Lessons -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">06. Lessons</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          I learned that decoupling CMS data models from static layouts makes codebases much more durable. I also discovered the importance of automating asset optimization at the CMS boundary.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>

    <!-- Tech Stack footer (mono, last) -->
    <footer class="flex flex-col gap-2 text-xs font-mono text-[#71717A] border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pt-6 mt-4">
      <span>Technologies: Next.js · Strapi CMS · PostgreSQL · Vercel</span>
    </footer>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
